<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1437878" src="https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/opeyemi.png?resize=587%2C572&#038;ssl=1" alt="Marry truthful single mothers than pretentious single ladies — Opeyemi Aiyeola" width="587" height="572" srcset="https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/opeyemi.png?w=587&amp;ssl=1 587w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/opeyemi.png?resize=300%2C292&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/opeyemi.png?resize=58%2C58&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/opeyemi.png?resize=199%2C194&amp;ssl=1 199w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/opeyemi.png?resize=133%2C130&amp;ssl=1 133w" sizes="(max-width: 587px) 100vw, 587px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> A popular Nollywood actress, Opeyemi Aiyeola, has urged men to marry truthful single mothers rather than pretentious single ladies. The actress, who took to her Instagram handle @opeyemi_aiyeola1 to give the advice, said that getting married to single mothers was far better than ladies who might have gone through abortions. Aiyola, also a producer and television personality, described ladies, who might have gone through the abortion process as ‘mother of graves’. “Better marry a truthful lady, after two or three or more, than marry a lady with seven abortions, pretending to be an angel; yet, she is a mother of graves …..unknown,” she wrote. The actress, who joined the Nigerian movie industry in 1998, acted in her first Yoruba movie “Aso Iye”. Ayeola, who rose to fame after acting in the Yoruba popular movie “Ige Adubi”, had scripted, produced and acted in several movies, including ‘Teni N Teni’, ‘Ige Adubi’, ‘Timileyin Oluwa’, ‘Onilara’, ‘Apaadi’ and ‘Adun Ife’, among others. In 2015, she won the award for Best Supporting Actress (Yoruba) at the Best of Nollywood Awards. Currently, one of the most talented and most influential actresses in Nigeria, Ayeola, in 2007, got married to Babatunde Owolomose and their marriage is blessed with two sons. She has a group called Opeyemi Aiyeola Rehearsal Group, which nurtures upcoming artistes. Aiyeola’s immense contributions to the entertainment industry have made her outstanding, coupled with the numerous movies she had acted. NAN Vanguard Sultry actress and mother of two, Opeyemi Aiyeola who  took a long break from acting immediately after she got married to her hubby, Olayiwola Abdulwakil Owolomonse in 2007,has announced her plans to stage a comeback to her first love-acting. January 27, 2018 In "Home Video People" It’s no longer news that veteran Nollywood actress and mother of two, Opeyemi Aiyeola, has been away from movie screens after getting married to her hubby, Olayiwola Abdulwakil Owolomonse, in 2007. January 27, 2018 In "Entertainment" Nollywood actress Ope Aiyeola has debunked rumours that she had a child in secret for veteran actor Babatunde Omidiran, a.k.a Baba Suwe. February 20, 2018 In "News"